article.description: Tim Abruzzo scored a career-high 16 points with a career-high five 3-pointers as Navy used a big first half to beat Furman 62-47 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Big first half helps Navy top Furman 62-47
article.linkText: Big first half helps Navy top Furman 62-47
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Tim Abruzzo scored a career-high 16 points with a career-high five 3-pointers as Navy used a big first half to beat Furman 62-47 on Tuesday night. Tilman Dunbar scored 13 points, Jace Hogan added 10, and Will Kelly had three blocks for Navy (9-4), which outshot Furman 42 percent to 30 percent and outrebounded them 41-28, including 12-7 on the offensive end. Furman led briefly, but Shawn Anderson's jumper and 3-pointer sparked a 24-2 run and Navy led 29-11. Hogan scored nine-straight points and Navy led 36-18 at halftime. Anderson had four of Navy's 14 assists, and Hogan and Tom Lacey each grabbed eight rebounds. Furman used an 11-1 run to close within 58-47 with 2:38 to play and outscored the Midshipmen 31-26 in the half, but Hogan hit a free throw to seal it for Navy and time expired. Stephen Croone led Furman (6-6) with 13 points and John Davis III had four assists.
